description: From algo- +‎ -genic, wherein algo- refers to pain, and -genic indicates causation thereof.

adjectives.description: algogenic (comparative more algogenic, superlative most algogenic)

examples: We wish to study the algogenic effect of bee stings.

description: From algo- +‎ -genic, wherein algo- refers to an alga or algæ, and -genic indicates production thereby.

adjectives.description: algogenic (comparative more algogenic, superlative most algogenic)

entries.meaning: (sciences) Produced by an alga or algæ.
examples: The algogenic organic matter affects the efficacy of water treatment.
